There is also a command within `vcd` itself to create a Contingency Table, `vcd::structable()`: 


::: {.cell layout-ncol="2"}

```{.r .cell-code}
arthritis_table <- vcd::structable(~ Treatment + Improved,
  data = Arthritis
)
arthritis_table
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
          Improved None Some Marked
Treatment                          
Placebo              29    7      7
Treated              13    7     21
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
vcd::mosaic(arthritis_table,
  gp = shading_max,
  main = "Arthritis Treatment Dataset"
)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/mosaic-plot-using-vcd-1.png){width=2100}
:::
:::



